<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12204g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12204g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12204g"> 204(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> buck affair</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;esclave dit: &ldquo;Mon p&egrave;re, voici ce qui est au fond de l&apos;affaire du bouc que je t&apos;ai donn&eacute;: l&apos;une de mes chiennes et l&apos;une de mes ch&egrave;vres ont mis bas durant une nuit l&apos;une aupr&egrave;s de l&apos;autre; la m&egrave;re ch&egrave;vre, d&egrave;s qu&apos;elle eut accouch&eacute; de son chevreau, mourut; le petit de cette ch&egrave;vre t&eacute;ta la chienne pour se nourrir: c&apos;est lui le bouc que je t&apos;ai donn&eacute;.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[The slave said, &ldquo;My father, this is the whole story of the billy goat that I gave you: one of my bitches and one of my goats have given birth one after the other in the same night: the goat, immediately after giving birth, died; the little goat drank milk from the bitch: that is the buck that I gave you.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
